######### Types of arguments ########

# Positional aruments: 
# these are the arguments passed to the function in positional order.
# number of args and position of args must be matched.
# if we change the args position, result will change
# if we dont provide right number of args, we will get error

# Keyword arguments:
# we can pass the parameter values by using parameter names 
# here the order of args is not important, but number of args is important

# Default arguments:
# sometimes we can provide the default values to the parameters
# if function is addition(a,b)--> a and b both can default args can be simultaniously, 
# but if one is default and other one is not, then default has to be the last parameter in function. non-default arg should not come after default arg. 

# Variable length arguments (*arg):
# by using variable length args, we can pass any number of arguments to the function.
# using all the args, tuple will be formed.
# we can do addition(arg1,*arg), addition(*arg, arg1=10), 
# but we cant do addition(*arg1,*arg2), addition(*arg,arg1)

# Variable length keyword arguments (**arg):
# same as variable length argument we can pass multiple key value pairs as an argument to the function
# it will return dictionary 

