########## filter() function ########

# we can use the filter() to filter values from the given sequence based on some condition
# filter takes only two parameters, filter(function, sequence)
# length of filter() function output is always less than length of sequence
# function can be method or lambda function.
# this is the best place to use lambda function.
# return type of fileter function is always filter object. so we need to typecast it to list

######### map() function  ###########

# In map(), we can apply some function to each element in the sequence and generate new element.
# length of map() is always same as sequenece
# map(function, sequence)
# return type of fileter function is always map object. so we need to typecast it to list

